"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The DateFormatter in matplotlib is used to format the x-axis tick labels as dates. However, the DateFormatter is being used with the format '%d/%m/%Y' which is different from the format used to convert the date strings to datetime objects. The datestr2num function expects the date strings to be in the format that can be parsed by the DateFormatter, which in this case is '%m/%d/%Y'. But the DateFormatter is being used with the format '%d/%m/%Y'. This inconsistency will cause the dates on the x-axis to be incorrect.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< x = datestr2num([datetime.strptime(day, '%d/%m/%Y').strftime('%m/%d/%Y') for day in days])\\n---\\n> x = datestr2num(days)\\n> days_formatted = [datetime.strptime(day, '%d/%m/%Y') for day in days]\\n13c13\\n< ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter(\\\"%d/%m/%Y\\\"))\\n---\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(DateFormatter('%m/%d/%Y'))\\n\"\n}"